message: Certainly. The categorical columns in this dataset are gender, race/ethnicity, parental level of education, lunch, and test preparation course. These columns contain data that describe qualities or characteristics rather than numbers. For example, gender tells us whether the student is male or female. Race/ethnicity categorizes the student into different groups based on their racial or ethnic background. Parental level of education shows the highest level of education completed by the student's parents. Lunch indicates whether the student receives standard lunch or free/reduced lunch. Lastly, test preparation course tells us if the student completed a test preparation course or not.
